(1 - \phi^2)\phi'' + \phi(\phi')^2 =0.
\frac{\phi''}{\phi'} = -\frac{\phi \, \phi'}{1-\phi^2}
\frac{d}{dx} \log{\phi'} = \frac12 \frac{d}{dx} \log{(1-\phi^2)}
\phi' = A \left (1-\phi^2\right)^{1/2}
A
\frac{d\phi}{\left (1-\phi^2\right)^{1/2}} = A \, dx
\arcsin{\phi} = A x + B
B
\phi(x) = \sin{(A x+B)}
